Vice President Biden met with President Mauricio Macri of Argentina at the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland. They discussed strengthening bilateral ties through increased cooperation on commercial and trade ties, defense and security issues, and educational exchanges. They also agreed on the importance of Argentina's leadership in addressing climate change, increasing renewable energy development, and opening its energy sector to investment. Both leaders pledged to deepen the bilateral partnership to build a democratic, middle-class, and secure hemisphere.